data.content:
Created both files. Here's how it works:

**`SortableList.razor`** — Renders a `<ul>` with each item using your `ItemTemplate`, plus Move Up/Down buttons (disabled at boundaries).

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** — Key design points:
- **Generic** (`TItem`) — works with any type
- **Internal copy** — `_items` is cloned from `Items` in `SetParametersAsync`, so the parent's list is never mutated
- **`OnOrderChanged`** — fires after each swap, passing a read-only copy of the reordered list

Usage matches your example exactly:

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskItem> tasks = new() { ... };

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
